<p>V. Baudelaire, Preface to <em>Fleurs du Mal</em>.
        [Eliot's note] The passage is the last line of the
        introductory poem "Au Lecteur" ("To the
        Reader") in Baudelaire's <em>Fleurs du Mal</em>.
        "Au Lecteur" describes man as sunk in
        stupidity, sin, and evil, but the worst in "each
        man's foul menagerie of sin" is boredom, the
        "monstre delicat" - "You know him,
        reader". </p>
